# ISIN Identification Process

## Objective

The purpose of this document is to identify the **ISIN (International Securities Identification Number)** for mutual fund schemes using the data received from **KFin (Karvy)** and **CAMS**.

> **Note:** The process of fetching the latest NAV and NAV Date using the ISIN will be handled by a separate process and is outside the scope of this document.

---

# Overview

```text
KFin/CAMS Files
       ↓
Product Code / ProdCode
       ↓
BSE Scheme Master (Channel Partner Code)
       ↓
ISIN
```

---

# 1. KFin (Karvy) ISIN Mapping

## Source Fields

### Folio Master

Field:

```text
Product Code
```

Example:

```text
Product Code = 105MSGP
```

### Transaction File

Field:

```text
fmcode
```

Example:

```text
fmcode = 105MSGP
```

---

## Mapping Logic

The value present in either:

* `Product Code` (Folio Master), or
* `fmcode` (Transaction File)

should be searched in the **Channel Partner Code** column of the **BSE Scheme Master**.

---

## Example

### KFin Folio Master

```text
Product Code = 105MSGP
Fund Description = JM Flexicap Fund - Growth Option
```

### KFin Transaction File

```text
fmcode = 105MSGP
Fund Description = JM Flexicap Fund - (Regular) - Growth Option
```

### BSE Scheme Master

| Channel Partner Code | ISIN         | Scheme Name                      |
| -------------------- | ------------ | -------------------------------- |
| 105MSGP              | INF192K01635 | JM FLEXICAP FUND - GROWTH OPTION |

### Final Mapping

```text
105MSGP → INF192K01635
```

---

# 2. CAMS ISIN Mapping

## Source Fields

### CAMS Folio Master

Field:

```text
PRODUCT
```

Example:

```text
PRODUCT = G340
```

### CAMS Transaction File

Field:

```text
PRODCODE
```

Example:

```text
PRODCODE = G340
```

---

## Mapping Logic

The value present in either:

* `PRODUCT` (Folio Master), or
* `PRODCODE` (Transaction File)

should be searched in the **Channel Partner Code** column of the **BSE Scheme Master**.

---

## Example

```text
PRODUCT / PRODCODE = G340
        ↓
BSE Scheme Master
        ↓
ISIN = <Matching Scheme ISIN>
```

---

# SQL Examples

## KFin

```sql
SELECT ISIN
FROM BSE_SCHEME_MASTER
WHERE CHANNEL_PARTNER_CODE = :product_code;
```

or

```sql
SELECT ISIN
FROM BSE_SCHEME_MASTER
WHERE CHANNEL_PARTNER_CODE = :fmcode;
```

---

## CAMS

```sql
SELECT ISIN
FROM BSE_SCHEME_MASTER
WHERE CHANNEL_PARTNER_CODE = :product;
```

or

```sql
SELECT ISIN
FROM BSE_SCHEME_MASTER
WHERE CHANNEL_PARTNER_CODE = :prodcode;
```

---

# End-to-End Flow

```text
KFin Product Code / fmcode
                OR
CAMS PRODUCT / PRODCODE
                    ↓
          BSE Scheme Master
                    ↓
                 ISIN
```

---

# Summary

| Source System     | Source Field | BSE Scheme Master Field | Output |
| ----------------- | ------------ | ----------------------- | ------ |
| KFin Folio Master | Product Code | Channel Partner Code    | ISIN   |
| KFin Transaction  | fmcode       | Channel Partner Code    | ISIN   |
| CAMS Folio Master | PRODUCT      | Channel Partner Code    | ISIN   |
| CAMS Transaction  | PRODCODE     | Channel Partner Code    | ISIN   |

---

# Output

The output of this process is the **ISIN**, which will subsequently be used by a separate NAV process to fetch the latest NAV and NAV Date.








